其說行這些事的

137
00:05:16,100 --> 00:05:19,000
則必因其活著」

138
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:22,000
基督既為我們受了奏助

139
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:25,200
則贖出我們脫離律法的奏助

140
00:05:25,200 --> 00:05:26,900
因為經上記著

141
00:05:26,900 --> 00:05:28,700
「凡掛在木頭上

142
00:05:28,700 --> 00:05:30,300
都是被奏助的」

143
00:05:30,300 --> 00:05:32,600
這便叫亞伯拉罕的福

144
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:36,600
因基督耶穌可以領導外邦人

145
00:05:36,600 --> 00:05:42,200
使我們因信得這所應許的聖靈

146
00:05:42,200 --> 00:05:45,000
Just as Abraham believed God

147
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:49,000
and it was credited to him as righteousness

148
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:50,800
So then understand that

149
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:53,900
those who believe are the sons of Abraham

150
00:05:53,900 --> 00:05:56,000
And the scripture foreseeing that

151
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:59,300
God would justify the Gentiles by faith

152
00:05:59,300 --> 00:06:03,000
proclaimed the gospel to Abraham ahead of time

153
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:06,700
saying all the nations will be blessed in you

154
00:06:06,700 --> 00:06:09,000
So then those who believe are blessed

155
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:13,000
along with Abraham the believer

156
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:17,100
For all who rely on doing the works of the law

157
00:06:17,100 --> 00:06:18,800
are under a curse

158
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:20,800
because it is written

159
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:25,600
Curseless is everyone who does not keep on doing everything

160
00:06:25,600 --> 00:06:28,200
written in the book of the law

161
00:06:28,200 --> 00:06:32,800
Now it is clear no one is justified before God by the law

162
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:36,400
because the righteous one will live by faith

163
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:39,000
But the law is not based on faith

164
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:43,000
but the one who does the works of the law

165
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:44,800
will live by them

166
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:47,400
Christ redeemed us from the curse of the law

167
00:06:47,400 --> 00:06:50,600
by becoming a curse for us

168
00:06:50,600 --> 00:06:52,100
because it is written

169
00:06:52,100 --> 00:06:56,500
Cursed is everyone who hangs on a tree

170
00:06:56,500 --> 00:06:58,300
In order that in Christ Jesus

171
00:06:58,300 --> 00:07:02,400
the blessing of Abraham would come to the Gentiles

172
00:07:02,400 --> 00:07:08,900
so that we would receive the promise of the spirit by faith

173
00:07:08,900 --> 00:07:12,900
Speaking of faith, we have to talk about Abraham

174
00:07:12,900 --> 00:07:15,900
But when we talk about the law

175
00:07:15,900 --> 00:07:19,500
we also have to mention Abraham

176
00:07:19,500 --> 00:07:22,500
Because in the book of Genesis

177
00:07:22,500 --> 00:07:27,000
we can see Abraham in chapter 15

178
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:33,700
that he can come to God by faith

179
00:07:33,700 --> 00:07:38,500
But in the book of Genesis 17

180
00:07:38,500 --> 00:07:44,100
we can see that God had told Abraham

181
00:07:44,100 --> 00:07:49,100
that all of his family members

182
00:07:49,100 --> 00:07:51,100
who belong to his family

183
00:07:51,100 --> 00:07:56,300
whether they are non-Jews or non-Christians

184
00:07:56,300 --> 00:07:58,300
should be sanctified

185
00:07:58,300 --> 00:08:02,100
So in the book of Genesis

186
00:08:02,100 --> 00:08:03,900
we can see that Abraham

187
00:08:03,900 --> 00:08:08,700
is not only an important figure in the discussion of faith

188
00:08:08,700 --> 00:08:12,100
but also, when it comes to the law

189
00:08:12,100 --> 00:08:15,900
we have to mention Abraham

190
00:08:15,900 --> 00:08:21,100
Although the Jews call themselves the descendants of Abraham

191
00:08:21,100 --> 00:08:28,500
they often promote the practice of the law

192
00:08:28,500 --> 00:08:31,900
So the Jews themselves

193
00:08:31,900 --> 00:08:39,100
actually also struggle between faith and action

194
00:08:39,100 --> 00:08:42,300
especially through the practice of the law

195
00:08:42,300 --> 00:08:44,900
which is a greater struggle for them

196
00:08:44,900 --> 00:08:47,700
But I believe that this kind of struggle

197
00:08:47,700 --> 00:08:51,300
is not only limited to the Jews

198
00:08:51,300 --> 00:08:54,000
especially every Christian

199
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:57,400
I believe that every Christian who believes in Jesus

200
00:08:57,400 --> 00:09:00,900
can become a Christian of God

201
00:09:00,900 --> 00:09:04,700
We also have this kind of struggle

202
00:09:04,700 --> 00:09:06,500
in our lives

203
00:09:06,500 --> 00:09:08,900
Because on the one hand, we have to claim

204
00:09:08,900 --> 00:09:12,300
that we directly believe in Jesus Christ

205
00:09:12,300 --> 00:09:14,700
and then we become a citizen of God

206
00:09:14,700 --> 00:09:18,100
But at the same time, it is very difficult for us to get rid of

207
00:09:18,100 --> 00:09:21,100
the various behaviors that have been left behind

208
00:09:21,100 --> 00:09:24,100
by religion and even the tradition of the Church

209
00:09:24,100 --> 00:09:26,500
We continue to repeat these behaviors

210
00:09:26,500 --> 00:09:30,700
in the history of the Church for more than 2,000 years

211
00:09:30,700 --> 00:09:31,700
Let us see

212
00:09:31,700 --> 00:09:33,700
In fact, the Christians also face

213
00:09:33,700 --> 00:09:38,500
a problem of faith and tradition

214
00:09:38,500 --> 00:09:40,300
And the tradition of the Church

215
00:09:40,300 --> 00:09:42,300
is also a kind of coercion

216
00:09:42,300 --> 00:09:47,700
that is very difficult for people to resist

217
00:09:47,700 --> 00:09:51,500
It is very easy for people to follow

218
00:09:51,500 --> 00:09:55,100
the tradition of the Church

219
00:09:55,100 --> 00:09:59,300
to create what we call a "sacred feeling"

220
00:09:59,300 --> 00:10:01,500
sacrificed feeling

221
00:10:01,500 --> 00:10:03,500
Therefore, many Christians

222
00:10:03,500 --> 00:10:06,500
rely on this kind of feeling

223
00:10:06,500 --> 00:10:09,300
to remain in the Church

224
00:10:09,300 --> 00:10:11,100
And the Church of Galilee

225
00:10:11,100 --> 00:10:13,900
under such circumstances

226
00:10:13,900 --> 00:10:17,300
It is very easy to take them away

227
00:10:17,300 --> 00:10:21,300
from the original recitation of faith

228
00:10:21,300 --> 00:10:26,700
and let them walk on a wrong path of faith

229
00:10:26,700 --> 00:10:29,300
Therefore, the book of Galilee

230
00:10:29,300 --> 00:10:32,100
whether it is the current Galilee Church

231
00:10:32,100 --> 00:10:34,500
or us today

232
00:10:34,500 --> 00:10:36,900
When we read the book of Galilee

233
00:10:36,900 --> 00:10:39,700
and see Paul write this letter

234
00:10:39,700 --> 00:10:42,900
it actually helps us a lot

235
00:10:42,900 --> 00:10:44,100
to make us understand

236
00:10:44,100 --> 00:10:51,300
the struggle between faith and behavior

237
00:10:51,300 --> 00:10:53,500
to make us learn

238
00:10:53,500 --> 00:10:57,900
how to accurately grasp the message of the gospel

239
00:10:57,900 --> 00:10:59,900
OK, since it is so important

240
00:10:59,900 --> 00:11:02,700
Let's go back and look at this passage

241
00:11:02,700 --> 00:11:04,300
I have just read this passage

242
00:11:04,300 --> 00:11:07,300
I will not read it in detail now

243
00:11:07,300 --> 00:11:10,100
But let me tell you

244
00:11:10,100 --> 00:11:12,500
why I will divide this Bible

245
00:11:12,500 --> 00:11:15,300
from the 6th chapter to the 14th chapter

246
00:11:15,300 --> 00:11:17,500
Many translations of the Bible

247
00:11:17,500 --> 00:11:19,100
You may have noticed

248
00:11:19,100 --> 00:11:21,700
Including the Bible of Genesis

249
00:11:21,700 --> 00:11:24,300
In fact, they also include the 6th chapter

250
00:11:24,300 --> 00:11:28,900
in the first 5 chapters of the Bible

251
00:11:28,900 --> 00:11:30,100
So to put it simply

252
00:11:30,100 --> 00:11:32,100
Many translators

253
00:11:32,100 --> 00:11:33,900
They think that the 1st to the 6th chapters

254
00:11:33,900 --> 00:11:35,700
should be a paragraph

255
00:11:35,700 --> 00:11:38,300
Then from the 7th to the 14th chapters

